cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network monitoring and failure identification. 
- cs.SI (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the design of monitoring schemes to optimize failure identifiability. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the problem of optimizing information obtained from path-level measurements. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the design of monitoring schemes to optimize system performance. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the problem of finding an optimal solution to a NP-hard problem.
